This paper deals with the theory of holographic algorithms, which is a subfield of computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The paper also involves counting problems, which are often studied in the context of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of planar perfect matchings suggests a connection to graph theory and combinatorics (cs.DM, cs.CG), while the mention of basis sizes and linear transformations suggests a connection to linear algebra and geometry (cs.GT).
